Topic 15 — Logging and Monitoring in Airflow

Why Logging Matters

In real projects, pipelines fail regularly.

Engineers spend major time on:

checking logs

debugging failures

tracing execution flow

identifying bottlenecks


Without logs:

You cannot debug pipelines properly.


---

What is Logging?

Logging records task execution details inside Apache Airflow.

Logs help track:

execution steps

errors

retries

task outputs



---

Logging Flow

Task Executes
      ↓
Logs Generated
      ↓
Stored by Airflow
      ↓
Viewed in UI


---

What Logs Contain

Logs commonly include:

task start time

task end time

print statements

exceptions/errors

retries

execution metadata



---

Accessing Logs

From Airflow UI

Flow:

DAG
 ↓
Task
 ↓
Logs


